Introduced by the President, by request.
- City Couneil 373 :

RESOLUTION NO.

A Resolution declaring that there is need for the estab-
lishment of a Re-Development Commission for the
City of Baltimore, as defined in Chapter 649 of the
Acts of 1943 and as defined by Sub-section (13A)
of Section 6 of Article 4 of the Code of Public
Local Laws of Maryland and Baltimore City
Charter (1938 Edition), title ‘‘Baltimore City?”’,
sub-title ‘‘General Powers’’, as said sub-section
was enacted by Chapter 664 of the Acts of 1943
and amended by House Bill 385, adopted by the
Greneral Assembly of the State of Maryland at the
1945 Session. .

-



By the Ciry Councin or Bartimore, April 9, 1945.

Introduced, read first time and referred to the Com-
mittee on Legislation.

By order, Epwarp P. O’MarLey, Chief Clerk.

*

REPORT OF COMMITTEE.
Favorable.
JEroME SromaN, Chairman,
CuarLes E. FavuTeER,
Erra A. Bangy,
Frank J. Bocek,
MaxweLL ALPERT,
James F. ArTHUR,
SamueL N. FrieperL,
Committee.
